    "levelAdaptation": "<div><p>After level 5: +5 Health, +D6 damage, +1 Armor (all Hit Locations except Chest)</p></div><div><p>After level 10: +D8 damage, +10 Combat Skill</p></div>",
    "actions": [
      {
        "startDie": 1,
        "endDie": 2,
        "name": "Gruesome Slam (Physical)",
        "description": "<div><p>The Amalgam swings one of its massive limbs at a target in a brutal, sweeping motion, dealing D6 Bludgeoning damage.</p></div>"
      },
      {
        "startDie": 3,
        "endDie": 4,
        "name": "Necrotic Burst",
        "description": "<div><p>The Amalgam's decaying flesh pulses with necrotic energy as it releases a burst of dark power. All creatures in the room must succeed on an Endurance check or take D6 Necrotic damage.</p></div>"
      },
      {
        "startDie": 5,
        "endDie": 6,
        "name": "Dismembering Strike (Physical)",
        "description": "<div><p>The Amalgam focuses its assault on a single target, attempting to tear them apart. It makes a melee attack against the target, dealing D6 Slashing damage. If the attack hits, the target must succeed on an Athletics check or be Restrained, as the Amalgam's gnarled appendages ensnare them. The target takes 1 Slashing damage at the start of their turns while ensnared. The Amalgam doesn't act against a character while they are affected by this Action; it will either change target or simply wait for the character to die or free themselves.</p></div>"
      }
    ],
    "description": "<div><p>Amalgams are grotesque and nightmarish undead constructs, a horrific fusion of multiple corpses and dark magic. These abominations are easy to recognize due to their body swollen and bloated from the sickening union of flesh and decay. Pieces of dismembered limbs and mismatched body parts jut out at odd angles, held together by taut, necrotic sinews that seem on the verge of tearing apart at any moment. The Amalgam's lumbering movements are slow but unyielding, causing the very ground to tremble beneath its immense weight.</p></div>",
